The disposition of "Other" is used to indicate several different dispositions. The Charge(s)/Sentence(s) and Court Record Events sections of the WCCA record display additional information that must be reviewed in order to determine the exact disposition of the charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz in court.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case was passed to the afternoon calendar to secure defendant's appearance.  Defendant has outstanding municpal warrants in the city of Glendale.  Defendant does not appear.  As the Extradition Unit of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department verified, there are no more open warrants in Chicago.  Therefore, State moves to close this case.  Defense counsel does not object.  Court granted State's motion and ordered this case closed.  Defendant is released from any requirements of bail on this case.  Cash bail on deposit to be returned to the person who posted same.

Attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz in court.  
Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Matter before the Court for status as to extradition.  Defendant in custody in Winnebago County in Illinois.  Defendant has warrant in Lee County.  Defendant scheduled to be turned over to Lee County.  The Court addresses time limits with counsel.  Case continued for status update.  Further proceedings scheduled for July 30, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Marissa L Shaw-White not in court, defendant in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Record made as to conference with the Court prior to this case being called; Attorney Schwartz was unable to appear at this time.  The parties advised the court that defendant is in custody in Illinois.  Parties requested the Court issue but stay a warrant.  Court granted joint request and issued but stayed a bench warrant before Branch 20.  Should defendant fail to appear on that date, bench warrant would issue.  Further proceedings scheduled for June 30, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz in court, defendant Marissa L Shaw-White not in court, in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel advised the court that his client has posted bail in this case and will be released at 10:00 a.m. today.  Defense counsel also advised this court that defendant has a court date in Illinois which may resolve this case.  Court continued matter before Branch 20.  Hearing scheduled for June 16, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Marissa L Shaw-White in court with attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Statements made by counsel and the Court.  Court granted joint request for the next court date to be set in May, after defendant's case is completed in Illinois.  Hearing scheduled for May 26, 2015 at 08:30 am.
